wpt.name: GC40C9
wpt.desc: Mayeski Cache by Siegfried & Francesca, Traditional Cache (2.5/2.5)

groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:name: Mayeski Cache
groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:short_description: Easy path for most of the journey, about a 1/4 mile hike.
groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:long_description: Located in a sports park, it is hidden back into a wooded area. Nice trails, but trailheads are not marked well. Enjoy the journey! GPS was a little erratic due to heavy fog/cloud cover ... but let it average for 15 minutes and it should be close.
groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:encoded_hints: A fallen dead tree, is the hiding place for me.

groundspeak:log.groundspeak:text:
Bit of a hot day for this one, but I persisted past the bugs and spider webs big enough to endanger small children and came away with the smiley while passing through the area. I was glad I had some water with me.
